Usually I'd go through and bullet point my thoughts, but generally I'd say it's a nice little treat. However, I have to wonder if you wanted to make a greentext instead of prose? Most of these paragraphs are short and simple, and the descriptions are relegated to short snippets made for a punchy, to the point kind of story. Which, I imagine it is, since it's porn (or would be?) about a guy fucking Wendy O. Koopa, but I feel like those punchy descriptions would be better fitted for an actual greentext. This is furthered by simple actions taking their own block, which seems odd and could easily be blended into the surrounding paragraphs. It's an aspect of greentext I never cared for, and if I had to describe it, it's like reading someone's secondhand accounts of what happened, if that makes sense. So I stick to writing prose myself.

I was actually interested in this amusing "world power leader" Bowser you had going on, with a regular schmuck going through it, but that's probably me attaching to silly details. Aside from that, I think you have a good grasp of amusing details and dialogue, and if you were to expand on your prose a little, I would be more than willing to read more. And of course, give feedback. I'm still pretty bad at it, but I hope this helps.
